metadata.othernotes:
COSTUMES
Noire's two costumes differ a lot in the stripping order, and she welcomes costume-specific targeted lines. Of course, lines that simply work for both of the costumes are great too.

SHORT SUMMARY
Noire is the goddess and ruler of Lastation, a country in the world of Gamindustri. She represents PlayStation consoles, but this is meta knowledge; it is not mentioned directly in the games and is unimportant for her character, especially in SPNATI. She is not a game console. She is a skilled gamer, though, despite not playing all that much. The source of her power are "shares", which are related to her popularity and the faith people have in her. They are mostly gained by doing quests, fighting monsters, and paperwork. Hardworking and diligent, she usually has more shares than the other goddesses. She fights with a sword, most often a rapier, and can use some magic. Before a battle, she usually transforms into her goddess (HDD) form (Black Heart). Her younger sister, Uni, who is a gunner and a goddess candidate (Black Sister), looks up to her, wishes to become a powerful goddess like her, and would love to be complimented on her progress, but it is not easy to be acknowledged because Noire demands from the others almost as much as from herself.
Noire puts up a cool façade to hide her tender personality. She tries to keep secret her hobbies, such as making clothes for herself, cosplaying (even though all the other goddesses already know about it), and performing as a Japanese-style idol (she does it openly only if the other goddesses do it too). She is often called a loner, and indeed she finds it hard to make friends, even though she wants to, because she is not honest with her feelings (sunao janai) and a tsundere (albeit with relatively weak tsun and stronger dere). She is pure and romantic and thinks about love the most often among Neptunia goddesses. She is willing to sacrifice a lot for people she cares about. She likes dark chocolate and the color black. She is also a dojikko.

In SPNATI: Noire already knows and likes or even loves the player (the player or player's avatar is basically a character in two of Neptunia spinoffs and meets each of the goddesses in VR scenes in one of the mainline games too), and she would do anything for him/her (more canonically him), even though she would never say so or acknowledge it. The player has helped her in the past, and she willingly accepts his/her invitation to the Inventory, despite knowing what game is going to be played. She is confident in her skills as a gamer, and in the first four stages she acts tsun, smug and victory-oriented (nevertheless, this is again mostly a façade, and she remains rather kind towards everyone). She wants the others to play fair and take the game seriously. As the game progresses, she gradually becomes more open with her feelings. She gets embarrassed a lot, but she also likes being the center of attention. She is much more comfortable around girls than around men (in Neptunia games there are no major male characters other than several antagonists, and so she does not have any male friends or acquaintances except perhaps the player).

TIPS FOR TARGETING NOIRE
– Especially if your character isn't from a fantasy setting, they don't necessarily have to believe Noire when she says that she's a goddess, she rules a nation, or that she fights monsters and robots. Noire doesn't do anything supernatural in SPNatI, and it's not certain that she has any godly powers on Earth.
– Noire likes video games and is very skilled at them, but it's not as important for her character as in the case of Neptune. She mostly plays them if the other goddesses play too, or if she's challenged by her sister.
– Noire won't normally say it and will try to hide it, but she makes her own outfits and loves cosplay, cute clothes, ribbons and accessories. Lines commenting on clothing are sometimes discouraged, but in the case of Noire they might work very well, as it's an important part of who she is. She'll be very happy if your character compliments her outfit. If your character is fashionable, their comments should be specific rather than general, to show their knowledge and interest in fashion.
– Noire likes compliments in general, praising either her abilities or her cuteness. Perhaps they can be used to win her favor.
– Neptunia is a lighthearted game series, so jokes and word plays are welcome. If you have an idea for a witty dialogue that requires Noire to say something specific, leave a note in the Character Editor – or write to me and we might discuss a whole six-line stripping segment at once instead of just sending lines one by one.
– If it's something your character would do, they may tease Noire and joke at her expense a little. Noire is very kind despite pretending to be cold, so it won't make her dislike your character. She might get embarrassed (which isn't a bad thing), and she either won't get angry or will get angry only slightly, in a cute way (I hope so). Neptunia goddesses joke at each other's expense all the time, and Noire is often at the receiving end of the jokes.
– Noire wants to make friends, but she finds it difficult to say what she really thinks, so she misses a lot of opportunities and remains lonely. She'll usually react positively to words like "friend" and "friendship". She's not as awkward as Yunyun, but it wouldn't be in character for her to befriend other characters in spnati too easily. Maybe it's OK if she doesn't become friends with your character; or maybe she won't even realize that they're gradually becoming friends; she doesn't think of the other goddesses as of friends even though they often play together and fight together against common enemies.
– Noire sometimes performs as an idol (look for "character songs" above to listen to three of Noire's songs and read the translations). In one of Neptunia games, the self-insert player character is her manager. There are episodes of her and the other goddesses becoming idols also in several other games and manga. She's also been a novice seiyuu and an amateur actress.
– Noire has a low Luck stat. Your character might notice it if she loses very hard (in spnati, she has the Average AI to reflect her high skills and bad luck).
– Noire is confident about her body and good looks (but it doesn't mean that she isn't embarrassed when she has to strip). However, if your character is very buxom, she might get slightly envious.
– All main characters and most of the supporting ones in the Neptunia series are female. Males are mostly either antagonists or very minor characters. That makes Noire much more comfortable around women and slightly wary of men, so if you're writing a male character and don't want Noire to distrust him, don't make him act too perverted, especially near the beginning of the game.
– Noire will decline all proposals of sex with a man that don't involve the ~player~. However, she might consider for example a threesome, allowing your character to watch as she has sex with the ~player~ or with a girl, or posing for a sexy cosplay.
– Noire is somewhat open to having sex with a girl who is not the ~player~. She would still like the ~player~ to join, but it's not completely required.
– Noire has no sexual experience and is mostly innocent but has some dreams and fantasies. As the game progresses and she loses clothes, she changes from tsun to dere and becomes gradually more excited, honest and willing to participate in a lewd conversation. She will react to some things differently in Stages 0-3, 4-5, 6-7, and 8. In Stage 9, she's calmer and less horny again.
– You're always welcome to message me if you want us to plan the dialogue or its part in advance, or if you have any questions or suggestions.

ADDITIONAL INFO: 1. THE SOURCES
The lore of Neptunia is complicated and likely internally inconsistent; there are parallel dimensions (worlds) and at least two Noires; one could speculate what exactly is canon; one could also try to differentiate between Noire from the Ultra Dimension (神次元) and Noire from the Hyper Dimesion (超次元). However, it is better not to think about it too deeply and certainly not to discuss the finer points of the lore in the dialogue. In order both to avoid these complexities and to be able to use as many of the sources as possible, I consider Noire in SPNATI as the unification of Noires from all the Neptunia games, including the spinoffs. She may reference anything that happened in any of the games, regardless of timelines, dimensions and so on (with a few exceptions; for example not the conquest ending of Neptunia mk2). Second in importance are the drama CDs, manga, anime, novels, artworks. They do inspire my portrayal of Noire's character (especially the drama CDs!), and may influence her art, but I consider most events depicted in them and not in the games not to "really" have happened.

ADDITIONAL INFO: 2. REASONS FOR MAKING NOIRE KNOW AND LIKE THE PLAYER

SPNatI is mostly about interactions between non-player characters; however, I felt that in the case of Noire, accepting the premise that she considers the player a friend would allow me to portray her in a more realistic way and show a greater part of her personality. As I want to argue, her friendship with the player does not preclude her trying to make new friends; on the contrary, in my mind's eyes it makes it easier. Noire isn't someone who finds it easy to befriend others or flirt with them in the first place, but if she feels comfortable enough, thanks to the presence of the player, she may try.
It is easy to come up with plausible reasons for all other Neptunia goddesses to enter the Inventory.
Neptune: just wants to have fun; likes all games; is carefree and probably cares little if she's naked; is usually low on shares and would like to try earning some in a fun way without paperwork (even if the attempt were destined to fail). Nutty did a good job showing all of that and aging up her behavior at the same time.
Blanc: enters in a disguise (i.e., wearing glasses) to learn something she may use when writing books and manga; may remove her disguise when she sees there is no reason to keep it; strips and watches people strip to experience what it feels like and thereby to become a better writer; at the same time, she wants to become more accepting of her own body and would be happy if people found her small breasts attractive.
Vert: is not an exhibitionist, but might want to play a game allowing her to show off her body.
Nepgear: could enter because someone, anyone, told her to; or to show that she's relevant.
Uni: wants to show by participating and winning the game that she's already mature and a full-fledged goddess (her understanding of maturity might still be a little naïve).
Plutia: could either enter to have fun without considering the details OR her Iris Heart personality could shine through, and she might seek sexual situations.
Now, Noire is the one who would be the least inclined to join.
Noire: does not like perverts (Anonydeath, who too her pictures from hidden cameras, is the antagonist she has the most trouble dealing with); more easily than the other goddesses gets embarrassed; is diligent and doesn't like to waste time; would like to make friends but is bad at it. Hypothetically, she could enter the game in order to make friends, but it's hard to imagine her that desperate, and if there were no friend of hers there to begin with, she could end up awkward like Yunyun or being mostly tsun for the whole game. On the other hand, she is willing to do anything for someone she already considers a friend. (It is vividly shown in a dialogue between Blanc and Noire in Neptunia: Producing Perfection. Blanc wrote for Noire a manga with the latter as the protagonist: in the manga, Noire gets betrayed by a friend but still believes in the power of friendship, and in the end sacrifices her life to protect the friend. Noire says it was a great story and wants Blanc to write a continuation.) I assume that if it's with a friend, Noire would be happy to play even if it's strip poker, and she would show a lot of her dere side; she'd be less awkward, and it'd be easier for her to try to make new friends too.

ADDITIONAL INFO: 3. LORE BASIS FOR MAKING NOIRE KNOW AND LIKE THE PLAYER

Noire is by far the most player-centric character in all of Neptunia franchise. By adding new generic and targeted lines, gradually I am going to make her less focused on the player in SPNatI than she is now, but a certain level of this focus of hers is not unrealistic, arbitrary or out of character when we consider her portrayal in some of Neptunia games (not to speak of the drama CDs and her character songs).

1. In "her" game, Hyperdevotion: Noire, the self-insert player character becomes her secretary and friend. Compare for example "Blanc's" game, Blanc+Neptune vs Zombies, in which there is no self-insert player character at all.

2. Neptunia: Producing Perfection is a game constructed almost like a dating simulation, in which the self-insert player character (again!) helps the goddesses become Japanese-style idols. There are four main routes, depending on which of the goddesses the player chooses to help (by becoming her manager) at the start of the game. In Noire's route, at first, in a true tsundere fashion, she says she does not need the player's help and demotes him to a producer, but then she becomes closer to him than the other goddesses in their routes; the scenes are the most romantic, and she's the only one to kiss the player character at the end.

3. There are VR scenes in which a self-insert player character meets each of the goddesses in a main-series game, Neptunia VIIR, as well. To be fair, it is arguably Blanc whose events are the most romantic there (especially the one in which she explains a poem from Hyakunin Isshu, which is one of the most beautiful scenes in the whole franchise), but Noire reveals to the player some of her secrets hobbies, which she hides even from the other goddesses.

ADDITIONAL INFO: 4. CHARACTER SONGS

Here are some Noire's her character songs together with their English translations. I wrote the translations to keep the meaning and the sentence structure as close to the original text as I could, and not always something that sounds good in Japanese sounds good in a direct translation, but I think it's better to know what the songs are really about rather than read translations that are distorted and reworded for artistic purposes. The words in italics are in English in the original text too:

This song is about Noire's ceaseless vigilance as a goddess, her heart connecting with those who are in trouble, about the importance of courage, hope and following one's dream, and about her wish to find someone she'd love.

The "sustain" from the title is a simile comparing how she hears the voices calling for help and the wishes and hopes of her believers to a long resounding note piercing the sky.

The story is that the voice of the person she hoped to find, calling for help, connected with her heart. His courage gave power to her and to himself. He was rescued, they've found each other, and now they're together.

ADDITIONAL INFO: 5. NOIRE'S TYPICAL DAY

Noire is diligent and almost a workaholic.

She wakes up at about 5AM, exercises in the early morning, does paperwork, quests (hunting monsters, retrieving items), sometimes playtests games. She cleans her room by herself and she sometimes cooks and bakes. She doesn't have any servants. Her right-her woman is her oracle Kei. She discusses politics and other important matters with her, but there are probably ministers and administration somewhere in the background. She spends some time with her younger sister Uni, who also helps her with her work.

From time to time, Noire gives public speeches and the like (in such formal situations, she presents herself to the public in her goddess Black Heart form). Once in a while, she performs as an idol. She'd like to try working as a seiyuu, and so she sometimes does vocal practice.

Her main but secret hobby is designing and making costumes and cosplaying. She usually just dresses herself up in her room, in front of a mirror. She loves cosplaying in public, but she only does it if she can pretend that someone asked her to, and she somehow had no other choice.

She is proud of the results of her work and that her country has the most shares among the four countries of Gamindustri, but she really would prefer to work less and have more time for her hobbies.

~Erion
